sentence: The original participating parties were: the Soqosoqo Duavata ni Lewenivanua (SDL) and the Conservative Alliance-Matanitu Vanua (CAMV) (these two parties were already in coalition, comprising bulk of the present government), the Soqosoqo ni Vakavulewa ni Taukei (SVT) (which led Fiji's governments from 1992 to 1999), the Nationalist Vanua Tako Lavo Party (NVTL), and the People's National Party (PNP).
